        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.belleislefl.gov/administration/page/city-information"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The city’s first mayor, Ross Dexter, died while in office, prompting City Hall to be named “Dexter Hall.”",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        3
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.belleislefl.gov/administration/page/city-information"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Belle Isle is home to Lake Conway, one of Greater Orlando’s largest lakes.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        13
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Belle_Isle%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The southern part of Little Lake Conway, another large lake, also lies within Belle Isle’s borders.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        14
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Belle_Isle%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "Belle Isle’s original government operated from 1924 until 1928 before being deactivated.",
